---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base title="Courses">
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <h2 class="section-title">Courses</h2>
      <p class="section-lede">
        Courses taught at the Department of Electrical and Software Engineering,
        Schulich School of Engineering, University of Calgary.
      </p>

      <h3 class="courses-heading">Current &amp; Upcoming</h3>

      <div class="course-list">

        <div class="course-card">
          <div class="course-header">
            <span class="course-code">ENEL 585</span>
            <span class="course-term">Fall 2026</span>
          </div>
          <h4 class="course-title">Introduction to Power Electronics</h4>
          <p class="course-body">
            Principles and applications of power electronic converters, including rectifiers,
            DC–DC converters (non-isolated and isolated), and single- and three-phase inverters.
            Core topics: switch commutation, power semiconductor devices, pulse-width modulation,
            dynamic modelling and control, magnetics, losses, thermal management, and EMI.
            Includes laboratory work and a design project involving the analysis, implementation,
            and testing of a power electronic converter.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="course-card">
          <div class="course-header">
            <span class="course-code">ENEL 300</span>
            <span class="course-term">Winter 2027</span>
          </div>
          <h4 class="course-title">Electrical and Computer Engineering Professional Skills</h4>
          <p class="course-body">
            Introduction to the electrical and computer engineering profession: fundamentals of
            engineering design, testing, and product development; critical thinking and project
            management; hardware design. Projects span a range of electrical and computer
            engineering domains, with an emphasis on teamwork, rapid prototyping, and technical
            communication.
            See a <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/posts/the-engineering-atrium-became-a-live-test-ugcPost-7450649330052399104-MaDj/?utm_source=share&utm_medium=member_desktop&rcm=ACoAAAYjZ_MBlmqocBRxFQiUsJygy9lfCUY3V6A" rel="noopener" target="_blank">student project showcase</a> from a recent offering.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="course-card">
          <div class="course-header">
            <span class="course-code">ENEL 619.02</span>
            <span class="course-term">Winter 2027</span>
          </div>
          <h4 class="course-title">Advanced Topics in Power Electronics</h4>
          <p class="course-body">
            Modeling and control of three-phase, grid-connected power electronic converters for
            modern energy systems. Topics include converter modeling, modulation techniques,
            reference-frame control (dq and αβ), synchronization methods, and grid-following and
            grid-forming operation. Applications include solar photovoltaics, battery energy storage,
            and distributed energy resources. Combines lectures with a hands-on, project-based
            component using power electronics test platforms and hardware-in-the-loop simulation.
          </p>
        </div>

      </div>

      <h3 class="courses-heading">Past</h3>

      <div class="course-list">

        <div class="course-card">
          <div class="course-header">
            <span class="course-code">ENEL 585</span>
            <span class="course-term">Winter 2024 · Winter 2025 · Fall 2025</span>
          </div>
          <h4 class="course-title">Introduction to Power Electronics</h4>
        </div>

        <div class="course-card">
          <div class="course-header">
            <span class="course-code">ENEL 300</span>
            <span class="course-term">Winter 2025 · Winter 2026</span>
          </div>
          <h4 class="course-title">Electrical and Computer Engineering Professional Skills</h4>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>

<style>
  .courses-heading {
    font-size: 1.15rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--muted);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    margin: 2.2rem 0 0.2rem;
  }

  .course-list {
    margin-top: 0.2rem;
  }

  .course-card {
    padding: 1.4rem 0;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line);
  }

  .course-card:last-child {
    border-bottom: none;
  }

  .course-header {
    display: flex;
    align-items: baseline;
    gap: 1rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.25rem;
  }

  .course-code {
    font-weight: 700;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    color: var(--uc-red);
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
  }

  .course-term {
    font-size: 0.88rem;
    color: var(--muted);
  }

  .course-title {
    margin: 0 0 0.5rem;
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    font-weight: 650;
  }

  .course-body {
    margin: 0;
    color: #333;
    max-width: 72ch;
    font-size: 0.99rem;
  }
</style>
